97static void truncateWithEllipsis(String& string, size_t length)
98{
99 if (string.length() > length) {
100 string.truncate(length);
101 string.append(ellipsis);
102 }

105static FloatPoint localPointToRootPoint(const FrameView* view, const FloatPoint& point)
106{
107 return view->contentsToRootView(point);
108}
109
110static void contentsQuadToCoordinateSystem(const FrameView* mainView, const FrameView* view, FloatQuad& quad, InspectorOverlay::CoordinateSystem coordinateSystem)
111{
112 quad.setP1(localPointToRootPoint(view, quad.p1()));
113 quad.setP2(localPointToRootPoint(view, quad.p2()));
114 quad.setP3(localPointToRootPoint(view, quad.p3()));
115 quad.setP4(localPointToRootPoint(view, quad.p4()));
116
117 if (coordinateSystem == InspectorOverlay::CoordinateSystem::View)
118 quad += toIntSize(mainView->scrollPosition());
119}

121static Element* effectiveElementForNode(Node& node)
122{
123 if (!is<Element>(node) || !node.document().frame())
124 return nullptr;
125
126 Element* element = nullptr;
127 if (is<PseudoElement>(node)) {
128 if (Element* hostElement = downcast<PseudoElement>(node).hostElement())
129 element = hostElement;
130 } else
131 element = &downcast<Element>(node);
132
133 return element;
134}

136static void buildRendererHighlight(RenderObject* renderer, const InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Config& highlightConfig, InspectorOverlay::Highlight& highlight, InspectorOverlay::CoordinateSystem coordinateSystem)
137{
138 Frame* containingFrame = renderer->document().frame();
139 if (!containingFrame)
140 return;
141
142 highlight.setDataFromConfig(highlightConfig);
143 FrameView* containingView = containingFrame->view();
144 FrameView* mainView = containingFrame->page()->mainFrame().view();
145
146 // RenderSVGRoot should be highlighted through the isBox() code path, all other SVG elements should just dump their absoluteQuads().
147 bool isSVGRenderer = renderer->node() && renderer->node()->isSVGElement() && !renderer->isSVGRoot();
148
149 if (isSVGRenderer) {
150 highlight.type = InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Type::Rects;
151 renderer->absoluteQuads(highlight.quads);
152 for (auto& quad : highlight.quads)
153 contentsQuadToCoordinateSystem(mainView, containingView, quad, coordinateSystem);
154 } else if (is<RenderBox>(*renderer) || is<RenderInline>(*renderer)) {
155 LayoutRect contentBox;
156 LayoutRect paddingBox;
157 LayoutRect borderBox;
158 LayoutRect marginBox;
159
160 if (is<RenderBox>(*renderer)) {
161 auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer);
162
163 LayoutBoxExtent margins(renderBox.marginTop(), renderBox.marginRight(), renderBox.marginBottom(), renderBox.marginLeft());
164 paddingBox = renderBox.clientBoxRect();
165 contentBox = LayoutRect(paddingBox.x() + renderBox.paddingLeft(), paddingBox.y() + renderBox.paddingTop(),
166 paddingBox.width() - renderBox.paddingLeft() - renderBox.paddingRight(), paddingBox.height() - renderBox.paddingTop() - renderBox.paddingBottom());
167 borderBox = LayoutRect(paddingBox.x() - renderBox.borderLeft(), paddingBox.y() - renderBox.borderTop(),
168 paddingBox.width() + renderBox.borderLeft() + renderBox.borderRight(), paddingBox.height() + renderBox.borderTop() + renderBox.borderBottom());
169 marginBox = LayoutRect(borderBox.x() - margins.left(), borderBox.y() - margins.top(),
170 borderBox.width() + margins.left() + margins.right(), borderBox.height() + margins.top() + margins.bottom());
171 } else {
172 auto& renderInline = downcast<RenderInline>(*renderer);
173
174 // RenderInline's bounding box includes padding and borders, excludes margins.
175 borderBox = renderInline.linesBoundingBox();
176 paddingBox = LayoutRect(borderBox.x() + renderInline.borderLeft(), borderBox.y() + renderInline.borderTop(),
177 borderBox.width() - renderInline.borderLeft() - renderInline.borderRight(), borderBox.height() - renderInline.borderTop() - renderInline.borderBottom());
178 contentBox = LayoutRect(paddingBox.x() + renderInline.paddingLeft(), paddingBox.y() + renderInline.paddingTop(),
179 paddingBox.width() - renderInline.paddingLeft() - renderInline.paddingRight(), paddingBox.height() - renderInline.paddingTop() - renderInline.paddingBottom());
180 // Ignore marginTop and marginBottom for inlines.
181 marginBox = LayoutRect(borderBox.x() - renderInline.marginLeft(), borderBox.y(),
182 borderBox.width() + renderInline.horizontalMarginExtent(), borderBox.height());
183 }
184
185 FloatQuad absContentQuad = renderer->localToAbsoluteQuad(FloatRect(contentBox));
186 FloatQuad absPaddingQuad = renderer->localToAbsoluteQuad(FloatRect(paddingBox));
187 FloatQuad absBorderQuad = renderer->localToAbsoluteQuad(FloatRect(borderBox));
188 FloatQuad absMarginQuad = renderer->localToAbsoluteQuad(FloatRect(marginBox));
189
190 contentsQuadToCoordinateSystem(mainView, containingView, absContentQuad, coordinateSystem);
191 contentsQuadToCoordinateSystem(mainView, containingView, absPaddingQuad, coordinateSystem);
192 contentsQuadToCoordinateSystem(mainView, containingView, absBorderQuad, coordinateSystem);
193 contentsQuadToCoordinateSystem(mainView, containingView, absMarginQuad, coordinateSystem);
194
195 highlight.type = InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Type::Node;
196 highlight.quads.append(absMarginQuad);
197 highlight.quads.append(absBorderQuad);
198 highlight.quads.append(absPaddingQuad);
199 highlight.quads.append(absContentQuad);
200 }
201}

203static void buildNodeHighlight(Node& node, const InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Config& highlightConfig, InspectorOverlay::Highlight& highlight, InspectorOverlay::CoordinateSystem coordinateSystem)
204{
205 RenderObject* renderer = node.renderer();
206 if (!renderer)
207 return;
208
209 buildRendererHighlight(renderer, highlightConfig, highlight, coordinateSystem);
210}

212static void buildQuadHighlight(const FloatQuad& quad, const InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Config& highlightConfig, InspectorOverlay::Highlight& highlight)
213{
214 highlight.setDataFromConfig(highlightConfig);
215 highlight.type = InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Type::Rects;
216 highlight.quads.append(quad);
217}

219static Path quadToPath(const FloatQuad& quad)
220{
221 Path path;
222 path.moveTo(quad.p1());
223 path.addLineTo(quad.p2());
224 path.addLineTo(quad.p3());
225 path.addLineTo(quad.p4());
226 path.closeSubpath();
227
228 return path;
229}
230
231static Path quadToPath(const FloatQuad& quad, InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Bounds& bounds)
232{
233 auto path = quadToPath(quad);
234 bounds.unite(path.boundingRect());
235
236 return path;
237}

239static void drawOutlinedQuadWithClip(GraphicsContext& context, const FloatQuad& quad, const FloatQuad& clipQuad, const Color& fillColor, InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Bounds& bounds)
240{
241 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
242
243 context.setFillColor(fillColor);
244 context.setStrokeThickness(0);
245 context.fillPath(quadToPath(quad, bounds));
246
247 context.setCompositeOperation(CompositeOperator::DestinationOut);
248 context.setFillColor(Color::red);
249 context.fillPath(quadToPath(clipQuad, bounds));
250}
251
252static void drawOutlinedQuad(GraphicsContext& context, const FloatQuad& quad, const Color& fillColor, const Color& outlineColor, InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Bounds& bounds)
253{
254 Path path = quadToPath(quad, bounds);
255
256 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
257
258 context.setStrokeThickness(2);
259
260 context.clipPath(path);
261
262 context.setFillColor(fillColor);
263 context.fillPath(path);
264
265 context.setStrokeColor(outlineColor);
266 context.strokePath(path);
267}
268
269static void drawFragmentHighlight(GraphicsContext& context, Node& node, const InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Config& highlightConfig, InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Bounds& bounds)
270{
271 InspectorOverlay::Highlight highlight;
272 buildNodeHighlight(node, highlightConfig, highlight, InspectorOverlay::CoordinateSystem::Document);
273
274 FloatQuad marginQuad;
275 FloatQuad borderQuad;
276 FloatQuad paddingQuad;
277 FloatQuad contentQuad;
278
279 size_t size = highlight.quads.size();
280 if (size >= 1)
281 marginQuad = highlight.quads[0];
282 if (size >= 2)
283 borderQuad = highlight.quads[1];
284 if (size >= 3)
285 paddingQuad = highlight.quads[2];
286 if (size >= 4)
287 contentQuad = highlight.quads[3];
288
289 if (!marginQuad.boundingBoxIsEmpty() && marginQuad != borderQuad && highlight.marginColor.isVisible())
290 drawOutlinedQuadWithClip(context, marginQuad, borderQuad, highlight.marginColor, bounds);
291
292 if (!borderQuad.boundingBoxIsEmpty() && borderQuad != paddingQuad && highlight.borderColor.isVisible())
293 drawOutlinedQuadWithClip(context, borderQuad, paddingQuad, highlight.borderColor, bounds);
294
295 if (!paddingQuad.boundingBoxIsEmpty() && paddingQuad != contentQuad && highlight.paddingColor.isVisible())
296 drawOutlinedQuadWithClip(context, paddingQuad, contentQuad, highlight.paddingColor, bounds);
297
298 if (!contentQuad.boundingBoxIsEmpty() && (highlight.contentColor.isVisible() || highlight.contentOutlineColor.isVisible()))
299 drawOutlinedQuad(context, contentQuad, highlight.contentColor, highlight.contentOutlineColor, bounds);
300}

302static void drawShapeHighlight(GraphicsContext& context, Node& node, InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Bounds& bounds)
303{
304 RenderObject* renderer = node.renderer();
305 if (!renderer || !is<RenderBox>(renderer))
306 return;
307
308 const ShapeOutsideInfo* shapeOutsideInfo = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer)->shapeOutsideInfo();
309 if (!shapeOutsideInfo)
310 return;
311
312 Frame* containingFrame = node.document().frame();
313 if (!containingFrame)
314 return;
315
316 FrameView* containingView = containingFrame->view();
317 FrameView* mainView = containingFrame->page()->mainFrame().view();
318
319 static constexpr auto shapeHighlightColor = SRGBA<uint8_t> { 96, 82, 127, 204 };
320
321 Shape::DisplayPaths paths;
322 shapeOutsideInfo->computedShape().buildDisplayPaths(paths);
323
324 if (paths.shape.isEmpty()) {
325 LayoutRect shapeBounds = shapeOutsideInfo->computedShapePhysicalBoundingBox();
326 FloatQuad shapeQuad = renderer->localToAbsoluteQuad(FloatRect(shapeBounds));
327 contentsQuadToCoordinateSystem(mainView, containingView, shapeQuad, InspectorOverlay::CoordinateSystem::Document);
328 drawOutlinedQuad(context, shapeQuad, shapeHighlightColor, Color::transparentBlack, bounds);
329 return;
330 }
331
332 const auto mapPoints = [&] (const Path& path) {
333 Path newPath;
334 path.apply([&] (const PathElement& pathElement) {
335 const auto localToRoot = [&] (size_t index) {
336 const FloatPoint& point = pathElement.points[index];
337 return localPointToRootPoint(containingView, renderer->localToAbsolute(shapeOutsideInfo->shapeToRendererPoint(point)));
338 };
339
340 switch (pathElement.type) {
341 case PathElement::Type::MoveToPoint:
342 newPath.moveTo(localToRoot(0));
343 break;
344
345 case PathElement::Type::AddLineToPoint:
346 newPath.addLineTo(localToRoot(0));
347 break;
348
349 case PathElement::Type::AddCurveToPoint:
350 newPath.addBezierCurveTo(localToRoot(0), localToRoot(1), localToRoot(2));
351 break;
352
353 case PathElement::Type::AddQuadCurveToPoint:
354 newPath.addQuadCurveTo(localToRoot(0), localToRoot(1));
355 break;
356
357 case PathElement::Type::CloseSubpath:
358 newPath.closeSubpath();
359 break;
360 }
361 });
362 return newPath;
363 };
364
365 if (paths.marginShape.length()) {
366 Path marginPath = mapPoints(paths.marginShape);
367 bounds.unite(marginPath.boundingRect());
368
369 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
370
371 constexpr auto shapeMarginHighlightColor = SRGBA<uint8_t> { 96, 82, 127, 153 };
372 context.setFillColor(shapeMarginHighlightColor);
373 context.fillPath(marginPath);
374 }
375
376 Path shapePath = mapPoints(paths.shape);
377 bounds.unite(shapePath.boundingRect());
378
379 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
380
381 context.setFillColor(shapeHighlightColor);
382 context.fillPath(shapePath);
383}

385InspectorOverlay::InspectorOverlay(Page& page, InspectorClient* client)
386 : m_page(page)
387 , m_client(client)
388 , m_paintRectUpdateTimer(*this, &InspectorOverlay::updatePaintRectsTimerFired)
389{
390}

392InspectorOverlay::~InspectorOverlay() = default;
393
394void InspectorOverlay::paint(GraphicsContext& context)
395{
396 if (!shouldShowOverlay())
397 return;
398
399 FloatSize viewportSize = m_page.mainFrame().view()->sizeForVisibleContent();
400
401 context.clearRect({ FloatPoint::zero(), viewportSize });
402
403 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
404
405 if (m_indicating) {
406 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
407
408 constexpr auto indicatingColor = SRGBA<uint8_t> { 111, 168, 220, 168 };
409 context.setFillColor(indicatingColor);
410 context.fillRect({ FloatPoint::zero(), viewportSize });
411 }
412
413 RulerExclusion rulerExclusion;
414
415 if (m_highlightQuad) {
416 auto quadRulerExclusion = drawQuadHighlight(context, *m_highlightQuad);
417 rulerExclusion.bounds.unite(quadRulerExclusion.bounds);
418 }
419
420 if (m_highlightNodeList) {
421 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_highlightNodeList->length(); ++i) {
422 if (auto* node = m_highlightNodeList->item(i)) {
423 auto nodeRulerExclusion = drawNodeHighlight(context, *node);
424 rulerExclusion.bounds.unite(nodeRulerExclusion.bounds);
425 }
426 }
427 }
428
429 if (m_highlightNode) {
430 auto nodeRulerExclusion = drawNodeHighlight(context, *m_highlightNode);
431 rulerExclusion.bounds.unite(nodeRulerExclusion.bounds);
432 rulerExclusion.titlePath = nodeRulerExclusion.titlePath;
433 }
434
435 for (const InspectorOverlay::Grid& gridOverlay : m_activeGridOverlays) {
436 if (auto gridHighlightOverlay = buildGridOverlay(gridOverlay))
437 drawGridOverlay(context, *gridHighlightOverlay);
438 }
439
440 if (!m_paintRects.isEmpty())
441 drawPaintRects(context, m_paintRects);
442
443 if (m_showRulers || m_showRulersDuringElementSelection)
444 drawRulers(context, rulerExclusion);
445}
446
447void InspectorOverlay::getHighlight(InspectorOverlay::Highlight& highlight, InspectorOverlay::CoordinateSystem coordinateSystem)
448{
449 if (!m_highlightNode && !m_highlightQuad && !m_highlightNodeList && !m_activeGridOverlays.size())
450 return;
451
452 highlight.type = InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Type::None;
453 if (m_highlightNode)
454 buildNodeHighlight(*m_highlightNode, m_nodeHighlightConfig, highlight, coordinateSystem);
455 else if (m_highlightNodeList) {
456 highlight.setDataFromConfig(m_nodeHighlightConfig);
457 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_highlightNodeList->length(); ++i) {
458 InspectorOverlay::Highlight nodeHighlight;
459 buildNodeHighlight(*(m_highlightNodeList->item(i)), m_nodeHighlightConfig, nodeHighlight, coordinateSystem);
460 if (nodeHighlight.type == InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Type::Node)
461 highlight.quads.appendVector(nodeHighlight.quads);
462 }
463 highlight.type = InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Type::NodeList;
464 } else if (m_highlightQuad) {
465 highlight.type = InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Type::Rects;
466 buildQuadHighlight(*m_highlightQuad, m_quadHighlightConfig, highlight);
467 }
468 constexpr bool offsetBoundsByScroll = true;
469 for (const InspectorOverlay::Grid& gridOverlay : m_activeGridOverlays) {
470 if (auto gridHighlightOverlay = buildGridOverlay(gridOverlay, offsetBoundsByScroll))
471 highlight.gridHighlightOverlays.append(*gridHighlightOverlay);
472 }
473}

529bool InspectorOverlay::shouldShowOverlay() const
530{
531 // Don't show the overlay when m_showRulersDuringElementSelection is true, as it's only supposed
532 // to have an effect when element selection is active (e.g. a node is hovered).
533 return m_highlightNode || m_highlightNodeList || m_highlightQuad || m_indicating || m_showPaintRects || m_showRulers || m_activeGridOverlays.size();
534}
535
536void InspectorOverlay::update()
537{
538 if (!shouldShowOverlay()) {
539 m_client->hideHighlight();
540 return;
541 }
542
543 FrameView* view = m_page.mainFrame().view();
544 if (!view)
545 return;
546
547 m_client->highlight();
548}
549
550void InspectorOverlay::setShowPaintRects(bool showPaintRects)
551{
552 if (m_showPaintRects == showPaintRects)
553 return;
554
555 m_showPaintRects = showPaintRects;
556 if (!m_showPaintRects) {
557 m_paintRects.clear();
558 m_paintRectUpdateTimer.stop();
559 update();
560 }
561}
562
563void InspectorOverlay::showPaintRect(const FloatRect& rect)
564{
565 if (!m_showPaintRects)
566 return;
567
568 IntRect rootRect = m_page.mainFrame().view()->contentsToRootView(enclosingIntRect(rect));
569
570 const auto removeDelay = 250_ms;
571
572 MonotonicTime removeTime = MonotonicTime::now() + removeDelay;
573 m_paintRects.append(TimeRectPair(removeTime, rootRect));
574
575 if (!m_paintRectUpdateTimer.isActive()) {
576 const Seconds paintRectsUpdateInterval { 32_ms };
577 m_paintRectUpdateTimer.startRepeating(paintRectsUpdateInterval);
578 }
579
580 update();
581}
582
583void InspectorOverlay::setShowRulers(bool showRulers)
584{
585 if (m_showRulers == showRulers)
586 return;
587
588 m_showRulers = showRulers;
589
590 update();
591}
592
593bool InspectorOverlay::removeGridOverlayForNode(Node& node)
594{
595 // Try to remove `node`. Also clear any grid overlays whose WeakPtr<Node> has been cleared.
596 return m_activeGridOverlays.removeAllMatching([&] (const InspectorOverlay::Grid& gridOverlay) {
597 return !gridOverlay.gridNode || gridOverlay.gridNode.get() == &node;
598 });
599}
600
601ErrorStringOr<void> InspectorOverlay::setGridOverlayForNode(Node& node, const InspectorOverlay::Grid::Config& gridOverlayConfig)
602{
603 RenderObject* renderer = node.renderer();
604 if (!is<RenderGrid>(renderer))
605 return makeUnexpected("Node does not initiate a grid context");
606
607 removeGridOverlayForNode(node);
608
609 m_activeGridOverlays.append({ makeWeakPtr(node), gridOverlayConfig });
610
611 update();
612
613 return { };
614}
615
616ErrorStringOr<void> InspectorOverlay::clearGridOverlayForNode(Node& node)
617{
618 if (!removeGridOverlayForNode(node))
619 return makeUnexpected("No grid overlay exists for the node, so cannot clear.");
620
621 update();
622
623 return { };
624}
625
626void InspectorOverlay::clearAllGridOverlays()
627{
628 m_activeGridOverlays.clear();
629
630 update();
631}
632
633void InspectorOverlay::updatePaintRectsTimerFired()
634{
635 MonotonicTime now = MonotonicTime::now();
636 bool rectsChanged = false;
637 while (!m_paintRects.isEmpty() && m_paintRects.first().first < now) {
638 m_paintRects.removeFirst();
639 rectsChanged = true;
640 }
641
642 if (m_paintRects.isEmpty())
643 m_paintRectUpdateTimer.stop();
644
645 if (rectsChanged)
646 update();
647}
648
649InspectorOverlay::RulerExclusion InspectorOverlay::drawNodeHighlight(GraphicsContext& context, Node& node)
650{
651 RulerExclusion rulerExclusion;
652
653 drawFragmentHighlight(context, node, m_nodeHighlightConfig, rulerExclusion.bounds);
654
655 if (m_nodeHighlightConfig.showInfo)
656 drawShapeHighlight(context, node, rulerExclusion.bounds);
657
658 if (m_showRulers || m_showRulersDuringElementSelection)
659 drawBounds(context, rulerExclusion.bounds);
660
661 // Ensure that the title information is drawn after the bounds.
662 if (m_nodeHighlightConfig.showInfo)
663 rulerExclusion.titlePath = drawElementTitle(context, node, rulerExclusion.bounds);
664
665 // Note: since grid overlays may cover the entire viewport with little lines, grid overlay bounds
666 // are not considered as part of the combined bounds used as the ruler exclusion area.
667
668 return rulerExclusion;
669}
670
671InspectorOverlay::RulerExclusion InspectorOverlay::drawQuadHighlight(GraphicsContext& context, const FloatQuad& quad)
672{
673 RulerExclusion rulerExclusion;
674
675 InspectorOverlay::Highlight highlight;
676 buildQuadHighlight(quad, m_quadHighlightConfig, highlight);
677
678 if (highlight.quads.size() >= 1) {
679 drawOutlinedQuad(context, highlight.quads[0], highlight.contentColor, highlight.contentOutlineColor, rulerExclusion.bounds);
680
681 if (m_showRulers || m_showRulersDuringElementSelection)
682 drawBounds(context, rulerExclusion.bounds);
683 }
684
685 return rulerExclusion;
686}

699void InspectorOverlay::drawBounds(GraphicsContext& context, const InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Bounds& bounds)
700{
701 FrameView* pageView = m_page.mainFrame().view();
702 FloatSize viewportSize = pageView->sizeForVisibleContent();
703 FloatSize contentInset(0, pageView->topContentInset(ScrollView::TopContentInsetType::WebCoreOrPlatformContentInset));
704
705 Path path;
706
707 if (bounds.y() > contentInset.height()) {
708 path.moveTo({ bounds.x(), bounds.y() });
709 path.addLineTo({ bounds.x(), contentInset.height() });
710
711 path.moveTo({ bounds.maxX(), bounds.y() });
712 path.addLineTo({ bounds.maxX(), contentInset.height() });
713 }
714
715 if (bounds.maxY() < viewportSize.height()) {
716 path.moveTo({ bounds.x(), viewportSize.height() });
717 path.addLineTo({ bounds.x(), bounds.maxY() });
718
719 path.moveTo({ bounds.maxX(), viewportSize.height() });
720 path.addLineTo({ bounds.maxX(), bounds.maxY() });
721 }
722
723 if (bounds.x() > contentInset.width()) {
724 path.moveTo({ bounds.x(), bounds.y() });
725 path.addLineTo({ contentInset.width(), bounds.y() });
726
727 path.moveTo({ bounds.x(), bounds.maxY() });
728 path.addLineTo({ contentInset.width(), bounds.maxY() });
729 }
730
731 if (bounds.maxX() < viewportSize.width()) {
732 path.moveTo({ bounds.maxX(), bounds.y() });
733 path.addLineTo({ viewportSize.width(), bounds.y() });
734
735 path.moveTo({ bounds.maxX(), bounds.maxY() });
736 path.addLineTo({ viewportSize.width(), bounds.maxY() });
737 }
738
739 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
740
741 context.setStrokeThickness(1);
742
743 constexpr auto boundsColor = Color::red.colorWithAlphaByte(153);
744 context.setStrokeColor(boundsColor);
745
746 context.strokePath(path);
747}
748
749void InspectorOverlay::drawRulers(GraphicsContext& context, const InspectorOverlay::RulerExclusion& rulerExclusion)
750{
751 constexpr auto rulerBackgroundColor = Color::white.colorWithAlphaByte(153);
752 constexpr auto lightRulerColor = Color::black.colorWithAlphaByte(51);
753 constexpr auto darkRulerColor = Color::black.colorWithAlphaByte(128);
754
755 IntPoint scrollOffset;
756
757 FrameView* pageView = m_page.mainFrame().view();
758 if (!pageView->delegatesScrolling())
759 scrollOffset = pageView->visibleContentRect().location();
760
761 FloatSize viewportSize = pageView->sizeForVisibleContent();
762 FloatSize contentInset(0, pageView->topContentInset(ScrollView::TopContentInsetType::WebCoreOrPlatformContentInset));
763 float pageScaleFactor = m_page.pageScaleFactor();
764 float pageZoomFactor = m_page.mainFrame().pageZoomFactor();
765
766 float pageFactor = pageZoomFactor * pageScaleFactor;
767 float scrollX = scrollOffset.x() * pageScaleFactor;
768 float scrollY = scrollOffset.y() * pageScaleFactor;
769
770 const auto zoom = [&] (float value) -> float {
771 return value * pageFactor;
772 };
773
774 const auto unzoom = [&] (float value) -> float {
775 return value / pageFactor;
776 };
777
778 const auto multipleBelow = [&] (float value, float step) -> float {
779 return value - std::fmod(value, step);
780 };
781
782 float width = viewportSize.width() / pageFactor;
783 float height = viewportSize.height() / pageFactor;
784 float minX = unzoom(scrollX);
785 float minY = unzoom(scrollY);
786 float maxX = minX + width;
787 float maxY = minY + height;
788
789 bool drawTopEdge = true;
790 bool drawLeftEdge = true;
791
792 // Determine which side (top/bottom and left/right) to draw the rulers.
793 {
794 FloatRect topEdge(contentInset.width(), contentInset.height(), zoom(width) - contentInset.width(), rulerSize);
795 FloatRect bottomEdge(contentInset.width(), zoom(height) - rulerSize, zoom(width) - contentInset.width(), rulerSize);
796 drawTopEdge = !rulerExclusion.bounds.intersects(topEdge) || rulerExclusion.bounds.intersects(bottomEdge);
797
798 FloatRect rightEdge(zoom(width) - rulerSize, contentInset.height(), rulerSize, zoom(height) - contentInset.height());
799 FloatRect leftEdge(contentInset.width(), contentInset.height(), rulerSize, zoom(height) - contentInset.height());
800 drawLeftEdge = !rulerExclusion.bounds.intersects(leftEdge) || rulerExclusion.bounds.intersects(rightEdge);
801 }
802
803 float cornerX = drawLeftEdge ? contentInset.width() : zoom(width) - rulerSize;
804 float cornerY = drawTopEdge ? contentInset.height() : zoom(height) - rulerSize;
805
806 // Draw backgrounds.
807 {
808 GraphicsContextStateSaver backgroundStateSaver(context);
809
810 context.setFillColor(rulerBackgroundColor);
811
812 context.fillRect({ cornerX, cornerY, rulerSize, rulerSize });
813
814 if (drawLeftEdge)
815 context.fillRect({ cornerX + rulerSize, cornerY, zoom(width) - cornerX - rulerSize, rulerSize });
816 else
817 context.fillRect({ contentInset.width(), cornerY, cornerX - contentInset.width(), rulerSize });
818
819 if (drawTopEdge)
820 context.fillRect({ cornerX, cornerY + rulerSize, rulerSize, zoom(height) - cornerY - rulerSize });
821 else
822 context.fillRect({ cornerX, contentInset.height(), rulerSize, cornerY - contentInset.height() });
823 }
824
825 // Draw lines.
826 {
827 FontCascadeDescription fontDescription;
828 fontDescription.setOneFamily(m_page.settings().sansSerifFontFamily());
829 fontDescription.setComputedSize(10);
830
831 FontCascade font(WTFMove(fontDescription), 0, 0);
832 font.update(nullptr);
833
834 GraphicsContextStateSaver lineStateSaver(context);
835
836 context.setFillColor(darkRulerColor);
837 context.setStrokeThickness(1);
838
839 // Draw horizontal ruler.
840 {
841 GraphicsContextStateSaver horizontalRulerStateSaver(context);
842
843 context.translate(contentInset.width() - scrollX + 0.5f, cornerY - scrollY);
844
845 for (float x = multipleBelow(minX, rulerSubStepIncrement); x < maxX; x += rulerSubStepIncrement) {
846 if (!x && !scrollX)
847 continue;
848
849 Path path;
850 path.moveTo({ zoom(x), drawTopEdge ? scrollY : scrollY + rulerSize });
851
852 float lineLength = 0.0f;
853 if (std::fmod(x, rulerStepIncrement)) {
854 lineLength = rulerSubStepLength;
855 context.setStrokeColor(lightRulerColor);
856 } else {
857 lineLength = std::fmod(x, rulerStepIncrement * 2) ? rulerSubStepLength : rulerStepLength;
858 context.setStrokeColor(darkRulerColor);
859 }
860 path.addLineTo({ zoom(x), scrollY + (drawTopEdge ? lineLength : rulerSize - lineLength) });
861
862 context.strokePath(path);
863 }
864
865 // Draw labels.
866 for (float x = multipleBelow(minX, rulerStepIncrement * 2); x < maxX; x += rulerStepIncrement * 2) {
867 if (!x && !scrollX)
868 continue;
869
870 GraphicsContextStateSaver verticalLabelStateSaver(context);
871 context.translate(zoom(x) + 0.5f, scrollY);
872 context.drawText(font, TextRun(String::number(x)), { 2, drawTopEdge ? rulerLabelSize : rulerLabelSize - rulerSize + font.fontMetrics().height() - 1.0f });
873 }
874 }
875
876 // Draw vertical ruler.
877 {
878 GraphicsContextStateSaver veritcalRulerStateSaver(context);
879
880 context.translate(cornerX - scrollX, contentInset.height() - scrollY + 0.5f);
881
882 for (float y = multipleBelow(minY, rulerSubStepIncrement); y < maxY; y += rulerSubStepIncrement) {
883 if (!y && !scrollY)
884 continue;
885
886 Path path;
887 path.moveTo({ drawLeftEdge ? scrollX : scrollX + rulerSize, zoom(y) });
888
889 float lineLength = 0.0f;
890 if (std::fmod(y, rulerStepIncrement)) {
891 lineLength = rulerSubStepLength;
892 context.setStrokeColor(lightRulerColor);
893 } else {
894 lineLength = std::fmod(y, rulerStepIncrement * 2) ? rulerSubStepLength : rulerStepLength;
895 context.setStrokeColor(darkRulerColor);
896 }
897 path.addLineTo({ scrollX + (drawLeftEdge ? lineLength : rulerSize - lineLength), zoom(y) });
898
899 context.strokePath(path);
900 }
901
902 // Draw labels.
903 for (float y = multipleBelow(minY, rulerStepIncrement * 2); y < maxY; y += rulerStepIncrement * 2) {
904 if (!y && !scrollY)
905 continue;
906
907 GraphicsContextStateSaver horizontalLabelStateSaver(context);
908 context.translate(scrollX, zoom(y) + 0.5f);
909 context.rotate(drawLeftEdge ? -piOverTwoFloat : piOverTwoFloat);
910 context.drawText(font, TextRun(String::number(y)), { 2, drawLeftEdge ? rulerLabelSize : rulerLabelSize - rulerSize });
911 }
912 }
913 }
914
915 // Draw viewport size.
916 {
917 FontCascadeDescription fontDescription;
918 fontDescription.setOneFamily(m_page.settings().sansSerifFontFamily());
919 fontDescription.setComputedSize(12);
920
921 FontCascade font(WTFMove(fontDescription), 0, 0);
922 font.update(nullptr);
923
924 auto viewportRect = pageView->visualViewportRect();
925 TextRun viewportTextRun(makeString(viewportRect.width() / pageZoomFactor, "px", ' ', multiplicationSign, ' ', viewportRect.height() / pageZoomFactor, "px"));
926
927 const float margin = 4;
928 const float padding = 2;
929 const float radius = 4;
930 float fontWidth = font.width(viewportTextRun);
931 float fontHeight = font.fontMetrics().floatHeight();
932 FloatRect viewportTextRect(margin, margin, (padding * 2.0f) + fontWidth, (padding * 2.0f) + fontHeight);
933 const auto viewportTextRectCenter = viewportTextRect.center();
934
935 GraphicsContextStateSaver viewportSizeStateSaver(context);
936
937 float leftTranslateX = rulerSize;
938 float rightTranslateX = 0.0f - (margin * 2.0f) - (padding * 2.0f) - fontWidth;
939 float translateX = cornerX + (drawLeftEdge ? leftTranslateX : rightTranslateX);
940
941 float topTranslateY = rulerSize;
942 float bottomTranslateY = 0.0f - (margin * 2.0f) - (padding * 2.0f) - fontHeight;
943 float translateY = cornerY + (drawTopEdge ? topTranslateY : bottomTranslateY);
944
945 FloatPoint translate(translateX, translateY);
946 if (rulerExclusion.titlePath.contains(viewportTextRectCenter + translate)) {
947 // Try the opposite horizontal side.
948 float oppositeTranslateX = drawLeftEdge ? zoom(width) + rightTranslateX : contentInset.width() + leftTranslateX;
949 translate.setX(oppositeTranslateX);
950
951 if (rulerExclusion.titlePath.contains(viewportTextRectCenter + translate)) {
952 translate.setX(translateX);
953
954 // Try the opposite vertical side.
955 float oppositeTranslateY = drawTopEdge ? zoom(height) + bottomTranslateY : contentInset.height() + topTranslateY;
956 translate.setY(oppositeTranslateY);
957
958 if (rulerExclusion.titlePath.contains(viewportTextRectCenter + translate)) {
959 // Try the opposite corner.
960 translate.setX(oppositeTranslateX);
961 }
962 }
963 }
964 context.translate(translate);
965
966 context.fillRoundedRect(FloatRoundedRect(viewportTextRect, FloatRoundedRect::Radii(radius)), rulerBackgroundColor);
967
968 context.setFillColor(Color::black);
969 context.drawText(font, viewportTextRun, {margin + padding, margin + padding + fontHeight - font.fontMetrics().descent() });
970 }
971}
972
973Path InspectorOverlay::drawElementTitle(GraphicsContext& context, Node& node, const InspectorOverlay::Highlight::Bounds& bounds)
974{
975 if (bounds.isEmpty())
976 return { };
977
978 Element* element = effectiveElementForNode(node);
979 if (!element)
980 return { };
981
982 RenderObject* renderer = node.renderer();
983 if (!renderer)
984 return { };
985
986 String elementTagName = element->nodeName();
987 if (!element->document().isXHTMLDocument())
988 elementTagName = elementTagName.convertToASCIILowercase();
989
990 String elementIDValue;
991 if (element->hasID())
992 elementIDValue = makeString('#', DOMCSSNamespace::escape(element->getIdAttribute()));
993
994 String elementClassValue;
995 if (element->hasClass()) {
996 StringBuilder builder;
997 DOMTokenList& classList = element->classList();
998 for (size_t i = 0; i < classList.length(); ++i) {
999 builder.append('.');
1000 builder.append(DOMCSSNamespace::escape(classList.item(i)));
1001 }
1002
1003 elementClassValue = builder.toString();
1004 truncateWithEllipsis(elementClassValue, 50);
1005 }
1006
1007 String elementPseudoType;
1008 if (node.isBeforePseudoElement())
1009 elementPseudoType = "::before"_s;
1010 else if (node.isAfterPseudoElement())
1011 elementPseudoType = "::after"_s;
1012
1013 String elementWidth;
1014 String elementHeight;
1015 if (is<RenderBoxModelObject>(renderer)) {
1016 RenderBoxModelObject* modelObject = downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(renderer);
1017 elementWidth = String::number(adjustForAbsoluteZoom(roundToInt(modelObject->offsetWidth()), *modelObject));
1018 elementHeight = String::number(adjustForAbsoluteZoom(roundToInt(modelObject->offsetHeight()), *modelObject));
1019 } else {
1020 FrameView* containingView = node.document().frame()->view();
1021 IntRect boundingBox = snappedIntRect(containingView->contentsToRootView(renderer->absoluteBoundingBoxRect()));
1022 elementWidth = String::number(boundingBox.width());
1023 elementHeight = String::number(boundingBox.height());
1024 }
1025
1026 // Need to enable AX to get the computed role.
1027 if (!WebCore::AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled())
1028 WebCore::AXObjectCache::enableAccessibility();
1029
1030 String elementRole;
1031 if (AXObjectCache* axObjectCache = node.document().axObjectCache()) {
1032 if (AccessibilityObject* axObject = axObjectCache->getOrCreate(&node))
1033 elementRole = axObject->computedRoleString();
1034 }
1035
1036 FontCascadeDescription fontDescription;
1037 fontDescription.setFamilies({ "Menlo", m_page.settings().fixedFontFamily() });
1038 fontDescription.setComputedSize(11);
1039
1040 FontCascade font(WTFMove(fontDescription), 0, 0);
1041 font.update(nullptr);
1042
1043 int fontHeight = font.fontMetrics().height();
1044
1045 float elementDataWidth;
1046 float elementDataHeight = fontHeight;
1047 bool hasSecondLine = !elementRole.isEmpty();
1048
1049 {
1050 auto firstLine = makeString(elementTagName, elementIDValue, elementClassValue, elementPseudoType, ' ', elementWidth, "px", ' ', multiplicationSign, ' ', elementHeight, "px");
1051 auto secondLine = makeString("Role ", elementRole);
1052
1053 float firstLineWidth = font.width(TextRun(firstLine));
1054 float secondLineWidth = font.width(TextRun(secondLine));
1055
1056 elementDataWidth = std::fmax(firstLineWidth, secondLineWidth);
1057 if (hasSecondLine)
1058 elementDataHeight += fontHeight;
1059 }
1060
1061 FrameView* pageView = m_page.mainFrame().view();
1062
1063 FloatSize viewportSize = pageView->sizeForVisibleContent();
1064 viewportSize.expand(-elementDataSpacing, -elementDataSpacing);
1065
1066 FloatSize contentInset(0, pageView->topContentInset(ScrollView::TopContentInsetType::WebCoreOrPlatformContentInset));
1067 contentInset.expand(elementDataSpacing, elementDataSpacing);
1068 if (m_showRulers || m_showRulersDuringElementSelection)
1069 contentInset.expand(rulerSize, rulerSize);
1070
1071 float anchorTop = bounds.y();
1072 float anchorBottom = bounds.maxY();
1073
1074 bool renderArrowUp = false;
1075 bool renderArrowDown = false;
1076
1077 float boxWidth = elementDataWidth + (elementDataSpacing * 2);
1078 float boxHeight = elementDataArrowSize + elementDataHeight + (elementDataSpacing * 2);
1079
1080 float boxX = bounds.x();
1081 if (boxX < contentInset.width())
1082 boxX = contentInset.width();
1083 else if (boxX > viewportSize.width() - boxWidth)
1084 boxX = viewportSize.width() - boxWidth;
1085 else
1086 boxX += elementDataSpacing;
1087
1088 float boxY;
1089 if (anchorTop > viewportSize.height()) {
1090 boxY = viewportSize.height() - boxHeight;
1091 renderArrowDown = true;
1092 } else if (anchorBottom < contentInset.height()) {
1093 boxY = contentInset.height() + elementDataArrowSize;
1094 renderArrowUp = true;
1095 } else if (anchorTop - boxHeight - elementDataSpacing > contentInset.height()) {
1096 boxY = anchorTop - boxHeight - elementDataSpacing;
1097 renderArrowDown = true;
1098 } else if (anchorBottom + boxHeight + elementDataSpacing < viewportSize.height()) {
1099 boxY = anchorBottom + elementDataArrowSize + elementDataSpacing;
1100 renderArrowUp = true;
1101 } else {
1102 boxY = contentInset.height();
1103 renderArrowDown = true;
1104 }
1105
1106 Path path;
1107 path.moveTo({ boxX, boxY });
1108 if (renderArrowUp) {
1109 path.addLineTo({ boxX + (elementDataArrowSize * 2), boxY });
1110 path.addLineTo({ boxX + (elementDataArrowSize * 3), boxY - elementDataArrowSize });
1111 path.addLineTo({ boxX + (elementDataArrowSize * 4), boxY });
1112 }
1113 path.addLineTo({ boxX + elementDataWidth + (elementDataSpacing * 2), boxY });
1114 path.addLineTo({ boxX + elementDataWidth + (elementDataSpacing * 2), boxY + elementDataHeight + (elementDataSpacing * 2) });
1115 if (renderArrowDown) {
1116 path.addLineTo({ boxX + (elementDataArrowSize * 4), boxY + elementDataHeight + (elementDataSpacing * 2) });
1117 path.addLineTo({ boxX + (elementDataArrowSize * 3), boxY + elementDataHeight + (elementDataSpacing * 2) + elementDataArrowSize });
1118 path.addLineTo({ boxX + (elementDataArrowSize * 2), boxY + elementDataHeight + (elementDataSpacing * 2) });
1119 }
1120 path.addLineTo({ boxX, boxY + elementDataHeight + (elementDataSpacing * 2) });
1121 path.closeSubpath();
1122
1123 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
1124
1125 context.translate(elementDataBorderSize / 2.0f, elementDataBorderSize / 2.0f);
1126
1127 constexpr auto elementTitleBackgroundColor = SRGBA<uint8_t> { 255, 255, 194 };
1128 context.setFillColor(elementTitleBackgroundColor);
1129
1130 context.fillPath(path);
1131
1132 context.setStrokeThickness(elementDataBorderSize);
1133
1134 constexpr auto elementTitleBorderColor = Color::darkGray;
1135 context.setStrokeColor(elementTitleBorderColor);
1136
1137 context.strokePath(path);
1138
1139 FloatPoint textPosition(boxX + elementDataSpacing, boxY - (elementDataSpacing / 2.0f) + fontHeight);
1140 const auto drawText = [&] (const String& text, SRGBA<uint8_t> color) {
1141 if (text.isEmpty())
1142 return;
1143
1144 context.setFillColor(color);
1145 textPosition += context.drawText(font, TextRun(text), textPosition);
1146 };
1147
1148 drawText(elementTagName, { 136, 18, 128 }); // Keep this in sync with XMLViewer.css (.tag)
1149 drawText(elementIDValue, { 26, 26, 166 }); // Keep this in sync with XMLViewer.css (.attribute-value)
1150 drawText(elementClassValue, { 153, 69, 0 }); // Keep this in sync with XMLViewer.css (.attribute-name)
1151 drawText(elementPseudoType, { 136, 18, 128 }); // Keep this in sync with XMLViewer.css (.tag)
1152 drawText(" "_s, Color::black);
1153 drawText(elementWidth, Color::black);
1154 drawText("px"_s, Color::darkGray);
1155 drawText(" "_s, Color::darkGray);
1156 drawText(makeString(multiplicationSign), Color::darkGray);
1157 drawText(" "_s, Color::darkGray);
1158 drawText(elementHeight, Color::black);
1159 drawText("px"_s, Color::darkGray);
1160
1161 if (hasSecondLine) {
1162 textPosition.setX(boxX + elementDataSpacing);
1163 textPosition.move(0, fontHeight);
1164
1165 drawText("Role"_s, { 170, 13, 145 });
1166 drawText(" "_s, Color::black);
1167 drawText(elementRole, Color::black);
1168 }
1169
1170 return path;
1171}
1172
1173void InspectorOverlay::drawLayoutHatching(GraphicsContext& context, FloatQuad quad)
1174{
1175 GraphicsContextStateSaver saver(context);
1176 context.clipPath(quadToPath(quad));
1177 context.setStrokeThickness(0.5);
1178 context.setStrokeStyle(StrokeStyle::DashedStroke);
1179 context.setLineDash({ 2, 2 }, 2);
1180
1181 constexpr auto hatchSpacing = 12;
1182 Path hatchPath;
1183
1184 FloatLine topSide = { quad.p1(), quad.p2() };
1185 FloatLine leftSide = { quad.p1(), quad.p4() };
1186
1187 // The opposite axis' length is used to determine how far to draw a hatch line in both dimensions, which keeps the lines at a 45deg angle.
1188 if (topSide.length() > leftSide.length()) {
1189 FloatLine bottomSide = { quad.p4(), quad.p3() };
1190 // Move across the relative top of the quad, starting left of `0, 0` to ensure that the tail of the previous hatch line is drawn while scrolling.
1191 for (float x = -leftSide.length(); x < topSide.length(); x += hatchSpacing) {
1192 hatchPath.moveTo(topSide.pointAtAbsoluteDistance(x));
1193 hatchPath.addLineTo(bottomSide.pointAtAbsoluteDistance(x + leftSide.length()));
1194 }
1195 } else {
1196 FloatLine rightSide = { quad.p2(), quad.p3() };
1197 // Move down the relative left side of the quad, starting above `0, 0` to ensure that the tail of the previous hatch line is drawn while scrolling.
1198 for (float y = -topSide.length(); y < leftSide.length(); y += hatchSpacing) {
1199 hatchPath.moveTo(leftSide.pointAtAbsoluteDistance(y));
1200 hatchPath.addLineTo(rightSide.pointAtAbsoluteDistance(y + topSide.length()));
1201 }
1202 }
1203
1204 context.strokePath(hatchPath);
1205}

1218
1219Path InspectorOverlay::backgroundPathForLayoutLabel(float width, float height, InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection arrowDirection, InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition arrowEdgePosition, float arrowSize)
1220{
1221 Path path;
1222 FloatSize offsetForArrowEdgePosition;
1223
1224 switch (arrowDirection) {
1225 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Down:
1226 path.moveTo({ -(width / 2), -height - arrowSize});
1227 path.addLineTo({ -(width / 2), -arrowSize });
1228
1229 switch (arrowEdgePosition) {
1230 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading:
1231 path.addLineTo({ -(width / 2), 0 });
1232 path.addLineTo({ -(width / 2) + arrowSize, -arrowSize });
1233 offsetForArrowEdgePosition = { (width / 2), 0 };
1234 break;
1235 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle:
1236 path.addLineTo({ -arrowSize, -arrowSize });
1237 path.addLineTo({ 0, 0 });
1238 path.addLineTo({ arrowSize, -arrowSize });
1239 break;
1240 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing:
1241 path.addLineTo({ (width / 2) - arrowSize, -arrowSize });
1242 path.addLineTo({ (width / 2), 0 });
1243 offsetForArrowEdgePosition = { -(width / 2), 0 };
1244 break;
1245 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::None:
1246 break;
1247 }
1248
1249 path.addLineTo({ (width / 2), -arrowSize });
1250 path.addLineTo({ (width / 2), -height - arrowSize });
1251 break;
1252 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Up:
1253 path.moveTo({ -(width / 2), height + arrowSize });
1254 path.addLineTo({ -(width / 2), arrowSize });
1255
1256 switch (arrowEdgePosition) {
1257 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading:
1258 path.addLineTo({ -(width / 2), 0 });
1259 path.addLineTo({ -(width / 2) + arrowSize, arrowSize });
1260 offsetForArrowEdgePosition = { (width / 2), 0 };
1261 break;
1262 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle:
1263 path.addLineTo({ -arrowSize, arrowSize });
1264 path.addLineTo({ 0, 0 });
1265 path.addLineTo({ arrowSize, arrowSize });
1266 break;
1267 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing:
1268 path.addLineTo({ (width / 2) - arrowSize, arrowSize });
1269 path.addLineTo({ (width / 2), 0 });
1270 offsetForArrowEdgePosition = { -(width / 2), 0 };
1271 break;
1272 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::None:
1273 break;
1274 }
1275
1276 path.addLineTo({ (width / 2), arrowSize });
1277 path.addLineTo({ (width / 2), height + arrowSize });
1278 break;
1279 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Right:
1280 path.moveTo({ -width - arrowSize, (height / 2) });
1281 path.addLineTo({ -arrowSize, (height / 2) });
1282
1283 switch (arrowEdgePosition) {
1284 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading:
1285 path.addLineTo({ -arrowSize, -(height / 2) + arrowSize });
1286 path.addLineTo({ 0, -(height / 2) });
1287 offsetForArrowEdgePosition = { 0, (height / 2) };
1288 break;
1289 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle:
1290 path.addLineTo({ -arrowSize, arrowSize });
1291 path.addLineTo({ 0, 0 });
1292 path.addLineTo({ -arrowSize, -arrowSize });
1293 break;
1294 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing:
1295 path.addLineTo({ 0, (height / 2) });
1296 path.addLineTo({ -arrowSize, (height / 2) - arrowSize });
1297 offsetForArrowEdgePosition = { 0, -(height / 2) };
1298 break;
1299 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::None:
1300 break;
1301 }
1302
1303 path.addLineTo({ -arrowSize, -(height / 2) });
1304 path.addLineTo({ -width - arrowSize, -(height / 2) });
1305 break;
1306 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Left:
1307 path.moveTo({ width + arrowSize, (height / 2) });
1308 path.addLineTo({ arrowSize, (height / 2) });
1309
1310 switch (arrowEdgePosition) {
1311 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading:
1312 path.addLineTo({ arrowSize, -(height / 2) + arrowSize });
1313 path.addLineTo({ 0, -(height / 2) });
1314 offsetForArrowEdgePosition = { 0, (height / 2) };
1315 break;
1316 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle:
1317 path.addLineTo({ arrowSize, arrowSize });
1318 path.addLineTo({ 0, 0 });
1319 path.addLineTo({ arrowSize, -arrowSize });
1320 break;
1321 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing:
1322 path.addLineTo({ 0, (height / 2) });
1323 path.addLineTo({ arrowSize, (height / 2) - arrowSize });
1324 offsetForArrowEdgePosition = { 0, -(height / 2) };
1325 break;
1326 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::None:
1327 break;
1328 }
1329
1330 path.addLineTo({ arrowSize, -(height / 2) });
1331 path.addLineTo({ width + arrowSize, -(height / 2) });
1332 break;
1333 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::None:
1334 path.moveTo({ -(width / 2), -(height / 2) });
1335 path.addLineTo({ -(width / 2), height / 2 });
1336 path.addLineTo({ width / 2, height / 2 });
1337 path.addLineTo({ width / 2, -(height / 2) });
1338 break;
1339 }
1340
1341 path.closeSubpath();
1342 path.translate(offsetForArrowEdgePosition);
1343
1344 return path;
1345}
1346
1347static FloatSize expectedSizeForLayoutLabel(String label, InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection direction, float maximumWidth = 0)
1348{
1349 auto font = InspectorOverlay::fontForLayoutLabel();
1350
1351 float textHeight = font.fontMetrics().floatHeight();
1352 float textWidth = font.width(TextRun(label));
1353 if (maximumWidth && textWidth + (layoutLabelPadding * 2) > maximumWidth)
1354 textWidth = maximumWidth;
1355
1356 switch (direction) {
1357 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Down:
1358 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Up:
1359 return { textWidth + (layoutLabelPadding * 2), textHeight + (layoutLabelPadding * 2) + layoutLabelArrowSize };
1360 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Right:
1361 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Left:
1362 return { textWidth + (layoutLabelPadding * 2) + layoutLabelArrowSize, textHeight + (layoutLabelPadding * 2) };
1363 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::None:
1364 return { textWidth + (layoutLabelPadding * 2), textHeight + (layoutLabelPadding * 2) };
1365 }
1366
1367 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1368}
1369
1370void InspectorOverlay::drawLayoutLabel(GraphicsContext& context, String label, FloatPoint point, InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection arrowDirection, InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition arrowEdgePosition, Color backgroundColor, float maximumWidth)
1371{
1372 ASSERT(arrowEdgePosition != LabelArrowEdgePosition::None || arrowDirection == LabelArrowDirection::None);
1373
1374 GraphicsContextStateSaver saver(context);
1375
1376 context.translate(point);
1377
1378 auto font = fontForLayoutLabel();
1379 float textHeight = font.fontMetrics().floatHeight();
1380 float textDescent = font.fontMetrics().floatDescent();
1381
1382 float textWidth = font.width(TextRun(label));
1383 if (maximumWidth && textWidth + (layoutLabelPadding * 2) > maximumWidth) {
1384 label.append("..."_s);
1385 while (textWidth + (layoutLabelPadding * 2) > maximumWidth && label.length() >= 4) {
1386 // Remove the fourth from last character (the character before the ellipsis) and remeasure.
1387 label.remove(label.length() - 4);
1388 textWidth = font.width(TextRun(label));
1389 }
1390 }
1391
1392 FloatPoint textPosition;
1393 switch (arrowDirection) {
1394 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Down:
1395 switch (arrowEdgePosition) {
1396 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading:
1397 textPosition = FloatPoint(layoutLabelPadding, -textDescent - layoutLabelArrowSize - layoutLabelPadding);
1398 break;
1399 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle:
1400 textPosition = FloatPoint(-(textWidth / 2), -textDescent - layoutLabelArrowSize - layoutLabelPadding);
1401 break;
1402 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing:
1403 textPosition = FloatPoint(-(textWidth) - layoutLabelPadding, -textDescent - layoutLabelArrowSize - layoutLabelPadding);
1404 break;
1405 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::None:
1406 break;
1407 }
1408 break;
1409 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Up:
1410 switch (arrowEdgePosition) {
1411 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading:
1412 textPosition = FloatPoint(layoutLabelPadding, textHeight - textDescent + layoutLabelArrowSize + layoutLabelPadding);
1413 break;
1414 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle:
1415 textPosition = FloatPoint(-(textWidth / 2), textHeight - textDescent + layoutLabelArrowSize + layoutLabelPadding);
1416 break;
1417 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing:
1418 textPosition = FloatPoint(-(textWidth) - layoutLabelPadding, textHeight - textDescent + layoutLabelArrowSize + layoutLabelPadding);
1419 break;
1420 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::None:
1421 break;
1422 }
1423 break;
1424 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Right:
1425 switch (arrowEdgePosition) {
1426 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading:
1427 textPosition = FloatPoint(-textWidth - layoutLabelArrowSize - layoutLabelPadding, layoutLabelPadding + textHeight - textDescent);
1428 break;
1429 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle:
1430 textPosition = FloatPoint(-textWidth - layoutLabelArrowSize - layoutLabelPadding, (textHeight / 2) - textDescent);
1431 break;
1432 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing:
1433 textPosition = FloatPoint(-textWidth - layoutLabelArrowSize - layoutLabelPadding, -layoutLabelPadding - textDescent);
1434 break;
1435 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::None:
1436 break;
1437 }
1438 break;
1439 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::Left:
1440 switch (arrowEdgePosition) {
1441 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading:
1442 textPosition = FloatPoint(layoutLabelArrowSize + layoutLabelPadding, layoutLabelPadding + textHeight - textDescent);
1443 break;
1444 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle:
1445 textPosition = FloatPoint(layoutLabelArrowSize + layoutLabelPadding, (textHeight / 2) - textDescent);
1446 break;
1447 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing:
1448 textPosition = FloatPoint(layoutLabelArrowSize + layoutLabelPadding, -layoutLabelPadding - textDescent);
1449 break;
1450 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition::None:
1451 break;
1452 }
1453 break;
1454 case InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection::None:
1455 textPosition = FloatPoint(-(textWidth / 2), (textHeight / 2) - textDescent);
1456 break;
1457 }
1458
1459 Path labelPath = backgroundPathForLayoutLabel(textWidth + (layoutLabelPadding * 2), textHeight + (layoutLabelPadding * 2), arrowDirection, arrowEdgePosition, layoutLabelArrowSize);
1460
1461 context.setFillColor(backgroundColor);
1462 context.fillPath(labelPath);
1463 context.strokePath(labelPath);
1464
1465 context.setFillColor(Color::black);
1466 context.drawText(font, TextRun(label), textPosition);
1467}
1468
1469void InspectorOverlay::drawGridOverlay(GraphicsContext& context, const InspectorOverlay::Highlight::GridHighlightOverlay& gridOverlay)
1470{
1471 constexpr auto translucentLabelBackgroundColor = Color::white.colorWithAlphaByte(230);
1472
1473 GraphicsContextStateSaver saver(context);
1474 context.setStrokeThickness(1);
1475 context.setStrokeColor(gridOverlay.color);
1476
1477 Path gridLinesPath;
1478 for (auto gridLine : gridOverlay.gridLines) {
1479 gridLinesPath.moveTo(gridLine.start());
1480 gridLinesPath.addLineTo(gridLine.end());
1481 }
1482 context.strokePath(gridLinesPath);
1483
1484 for (auto gapQuad : gridOverlay.gaps)
1485 drawLayoutHatching(context, gapQuad);
1486
1487 context.setStrokeThickness(3);
1488 for (auto area : gridOverlay.areas)
1489 context.strokePath(quadToPath(area.quad));
1490
1491 // Draw labels on top of all other lines.
1492 context.setStrokeThickness(1);
1493 for (auto area : gridOverlay.areas)
1494 drawLayoutLabel(context, area.name, area.quad.center(), LabelArrowDirection::None, LabelArrowEdgePosition::None, translucentLabelBackgroundColor, area.quad.boundingBox().width());
1495
1496 for (auto label : gridOverlay.labels)
1497 drawLayoutLabel(context, label.text, label.location, label.arrowDirection, label.arrowEdgePosition, label.backgroundColor);
1498}
1499
1500static Vector<String> authoredGridTrackSizes(Node* node, GridTrackSizingDirection direction, unsigned expectedTrackCount)
1501{
1502 if (!is<StyledElement>(node))
1503 return { };
1504
1505 auto element = downcast<StyledElement>(node);
1506 auto directionCSSPropertyID = direction == GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns ? CSSPropertyID::CSSPropertyGridTemplateColumns : CSSPropertyID::CSSPropertyGridTemplateRows;
1507 RefPtr<CSSValue> cssValue = element->cssomStyle().getPropertyCSSValueInternal(directionCSSPropertyID);
1508
1509 if (!cssValue) {
1510 auto styleRules = element->styleResolver().styleRulesForElement(element);
1511 styleRules.reverse();
1512 for (auto styleRule : styleRules) {
1513 ASSERT(styleRule);
1514 if (!styleRule)
1515 continue;
1516 cssValue = styleRule->properties().getPropertyCSSValue(directionCSSPropertyID);
1517 if (cssValue)
1518 break;
1519 }
1520 }
1521
1522 if (!cssValue || !is<CSSValueList>(cssValue))
1523 return { };
1524
1525 Vector<String> trackSizes;
1526
1527 auto handleValueIgnoringLineNames = [&](const CSSValue& currentValue) {
1528 if (!is<CSSGridLineNamesValue>(currentValue))
1529 trackSizes.append(currentValue.cssText());
1530 };
1531
1532 for (auto& currentValue : downcast<CSSValueList>(*cssValue)) {
1533 if (is<CSSGridAutoRepeatValue>(currentValue)) {
1534 // Auto-repeated values will be looped through until no more values were used in layout based on the expected track count.
1535 while (trackSizes.size() < expectedTrackCount) {
1536 for (auto& autoRepeatValue : downcast<CSSValueList>(currentValue.get())) {
1537 handleValueIgnoringLineNames(autoRepeatValue);
1538 if (trackSizes.size() >= expectedTrackCount)
1539 break;
1540 }
1541 }
1542 break;
1543 }
1544
1545 if (is<CSSGridIntegerRepeatValue>(currentValue)) {
1546 size_t repetitions = downcast<CSSGridIntegerRepeatValue>(currentValue.get()).repetitions();
1547 for (size_t i = 0; i < repetitions; ++i) {
1548 for (auto& integerRepeatValue : downcast<CSSValueList>(currentValue.get()))
1549 handleValueIgnoringLineNames(integerRepeatValue);
1550 }
1551 continue;
1552 }
1553
1554 handleValueIgnoringLineNames(currentValue);
1555 }
1556
1557 return trackSizes;
1558}
1559
1560static OrderedNamedGridLinesMap gridLineNames(const RenderStyle* renderStyle, GridTrackSizingDirection direction, unsigned expectedLineCount)
1561{
1562 if (!renderStyle)
1563 return { };
1564
1565 OrderedNamedGridLinesMap combinedGridLineNames;
1566 auto appendLineNames = [&](unsigned index, const Vector<String>& newNames) {
1567 if (combinedGridLineNames.contains(index)) {
1568 auto names = combinedGridLineNames.take(index);
1569 names.appendVector(newNames);
1570 combinedGridLineNames.add(index, names);
1571 } else
1572 combinedGridLineNames.add(index, newNames);
1573 };
1574
1575 auto orderedGridLineNames = direction == GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns ? renderStyle->orderedNamedGridColumnLines() : renderStyle->orderedNamedGridRowLines();
1576 for (auto& [i, names] : orderedGridLineNames)
1577 appendLineNames(i, names);
1578
1579 auto autoRepeatOrderedGridLineNames = direction == GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns ? renderStyle->autoRepeatOrderedNamedGridColumnLines() : renderStyle->autoRepeatOrderedNamedGridRowLines();
1580 auto autoRepeatInsertionPoint = direction == GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns ? renderStyle->gridAutoRepeatColumnsInsertionPoint() : renderStyle->gridAutoRepeatRowsInsertionPoint();
1581 unsigned autoRepeatIndex = 0;
1582 while (autoRepeatOrderedGridLineNames.size() && autoRepeatIndex < expectedLineCount - autoRepeatInsertionPoint) {
1583 auto names = autoRepeatOrderedGridLineNames.get(autoRepeatIndex % autoRepeatOrderedGridLineNames.size());
1584 auto lineIndex = autoRepeatIndex + autoRepeatInsertionPoint;
1585 appendLineNames(lineIndex, names);
1586 ++autoRepeatIndex;
1587 }
1588
1589 auto implicitGridLineNames = direction == GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns ? renderStyle->implicitNamedGridColumnLines() : renderStyle->implicitNamedGridRowLines();
1590 for (auto& [name, indexes] : implicitGridLineNames) {
1591 for (auto i : indexes)
1592 appendLineNames(i, {name});
1593 }
1594
1595 return combinedGridLineNames;
1596}

1598static InspectorOverlay::Highlight::GridHighlightOverlay::Label buildLabel(String text, FloatPoint location, Color backgroundColor, InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowDirection arrowDirection, InspectorOverlay::LabelArrowEdgePosition arrowEdgePosition)
1599{
1600 InspectorOverlay::Highlight::GridHighlightOverlay::Label label;
1601 label.text = text;
1602 label.location = location;
1603 label.backgroundColor = backgroundColor;
1604 label.arrowDirection = arrowDirection;
1605 label.arrowEdgePosition = arrowEdgePosition;
1606 return label;
1607}
1608
1609std::optional<InspectorOverlay::Highlight::GridHighlightOverlay> InspectorOverlay::buildGridOverlay(const InspectorOverlay::Grid& gridOverlay, bool offsetBoundsByScroll)
1610{
1611 // If the node WeakPtr has been cleared, then the node is gone and there's nothing to draw.
1612 if (!gridOverlay.gridNode) {
1613 m_activeGridOverlays.removeAllMatching([&] (const InspectorOverlay::Grid& gridOverlay) {
1614 return !gridOverlay.gridNode;
1615 });
1616 return { };
1617 }
1618
1619 // Always re-check because the node's renderer may have changed since being added.
1620 // If renderer is no longer a grid, then remove the grid overlay for the node.
1621 Node* node = gridOverlay.gridNode.get();
1622 auto renderer = node->renderer();
1623 if (!is<RenderGrid>(renderer)) {
1624 removeGridOverlayForNode(*node);
1625 return { };
1626 }
1627
1628 constexpr auto translucentLabelBackgroundColor = Color::white.colorWithAlphaByte(230);
1629
1630 FrameView* pageView = m_page.mainFrame().view();
1631 if (!pageView)
1632 return { };
1633 FloatRect viewportBounds = { { 0, 0 }, pageView->sizeForVisibleContent() };
1634
1635 auto scrollPosition = pageView->scrollPosition();
1636 if (offsetBoundsByScroll)
1637 viewportBounds.setLocation(scrollPosition);
1638
1639 auto& renderGrid = *downcast<RenderGrid>(renderer);
1640 auto columnPositions = renderGrid.columnPositions();
1641 auto rowPositions = renderGrid.rowPositions();
1642 if (!columnPositions.size() || !rowPositions.size())
1643 return { };
1644
1645 float gridStartX = columnPositions[0];
1646 float gridEndX = columnPositions[columnPositions.size() - 1];
1647 float gridStartY = rowPositions[0];
1648 float gridEndY = rowPositions[rowPositions.size() - 1];
1649
1650 Frame* containingFrame = node->document().frame();
1651 if (!containingFrame)
1652 return { };
1653 FrameView* containingView = containingFrame->view();
1654
1655 auto computedStyle = node->computedStyle();
1656 if (!computedStyle)
1657 return { };
1658
1659 auto isHorizontalWritingMode = computedStyle->isHorizontalWritingMode();
1660 auto isDirectionFlipped = !computedStyle->isLeftToRightDirection();
1661 auto isWritingModeFlipped = computedStyle->isFlippedBlocksWritingMode();
1662 auto contentBox = renderGrid.absoluteBoundingBoxRectIgnoringTransforms();
1663
1664 auto columnLineAt = [&](float x) -> FloatLine {
1665 FloatPoint startPoint;
1666 FloatPoint endPoint;
1667 if (isHorizontalWritingMode) {
1668 startPoint = { isDirectionFlipped ? contentBox.width() - x : x, isWritingModeFlipped ? contentBox.height() - gridStartY : gridStartY };
1669 endPoint = { isDirectionFlipped ? contentBox.width() - x : x, isWritingModeFlipped ? contentBox.height() - gridEndY : gridEndY };
1670 } else {
1671 startPoint = { isWritingModeFlipped ? contentBox.width() - gridStartY : gridStartY, isDirectionFlipped ? contentBox.height() - x : x };
1672 endPoint = { isWritingModeFlipped ? contentBox.width() - gridEndY : gridEndY, isDirectionFlipped ? contentBox.height() - x : x };
1673 }
1674 return {
1675 localPointToRootPoint(containingView, renderGrid.localToContainerPoint(startPoint, nullptr)),
1676 localPointToRootPoint(containingView, renderGrid.localToContainerPoint(endPoint, nullptr)),
1677 };
1678 };
1679 auto rowLineAt = [&](float y) -> FloatLine {
1680 FloatPoint startPoint;
1681 FloatPoint endPoint;
1682 if (isHorizontalWritingMode) {
1683 startPoint = { isDirectionFlipped ? contentBox.width() - gridStartX : gridStartX, isWritingModeFlipped ? contentBox.height() - y : y };
1684 endPoint = { isDirectionFlipped ? contentBox.width() - gridEndX : gridEndX, isWritingModeFlipped ? contentBox.height() - y : y };
1685 } else {
1686 startPoint = { isWritingModeFlipped ? contentBox.width() - y : y, isDirectionFlipped ? contentBox.height() - gridStartX : gridStartX };
1687 endPoint = { isWritingModeFlipped ? contentBox.width() - y : y, isDirectionFlipped ? contentBox.height() - gridEndX : gridEndX };
1688 }
1689 return {
1690 localPointToRootPoint(containingView, renderGrid.localToContainerPoint(startPoint, nullptr)),
1691 localPointToRootPoint(containingView, renderGrid.localToContainerPoint(endPoint, nullptr)),
1692 };
1693 };
1694
1695 auto correctedArrowDirection = [&](LabelArrowDirection direction, GridTrackSizingDirection sizingDirection) -> LabelArrowDirection {
1696 if ((sizingDirection == GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns && isWritingModeFlipped) || (sizingDirection == GridTrackSizingDirection::ForRows && isDirectionFlipped)) {
1697 switch (direction) {
1698 case LabelArrowDirection::Down:
1699 direction = LabelArrowDirection::Up;
1700 break;
1701 case LabelArrowDirection::Up:
1702 direction = LabelArrowDirection::Down;
1703 break;
1704 case LabelArrowDirection::Left:
1705 direction = LabelArrowDirection::Right;
1706 break;
1707 case LabelArrowDirection::Right:
1708 direction = LabelArrowDirection::Left;
1709 break;
1710 case LabelArrowDirection::None:
1711 break;
1712 }
1713 }
1714
1715 if (!isHorizontalWritingMode) {
1716 switch (direction) {
1717 case LabelArrowDirection::Down:
1718 direction = LabelArrowDirection::Right;
1719 break;
1720 case LabelArrowDirection::Up:
1721 direction = LabelArrowDirection::Left;
1722 break;
1723 case LabelArrowDirection::Left:
1724 direction = LabelArrowDirection::Up;
1725 break;
1726 case LabelArrowDirection::Right:
1727 direction = LabelArrowDirection::Down;
1728 break;
1729 case LabelArrowDirection::None:
1730 break;
1731 }
1732 }
1733
1734 return direction;
1735 };
1736
1737 auto correctedArrowEdgePosition = [&](LabelArrowEdgePosition edgePosition, GridTrackSizingDirection sizingDirection) -> LabelArrowEdgePosition {
1738 if ((sizingDirection == GridTrackSizingDirection::ForRows && isWritingModeFlipped) || (sizingDirection == GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns && isDirectionFlipped)) {
1739 if (edgePosition == LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading)
1740 return LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing;
1741 if (edgePosition == LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing)
1742 return LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading;
1743 }
1744
1745 return edgePosition;
1746 };
1747
1748 InspectorOverlay::Highlight::GridHighlightOverlay gridHighlightOverlay;
1749 gridHighlightOverlay.color = gridOverlay.config.gridColor;
1750
1751 // Draw columns and rows.
1752 auto columnWidths = renderGrid.trackSizesForComputedStyle(GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns);
1753 auto columnLineNames = gridLineNames(node->renderStyle(), GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns, columnPositions.size());
1754 auto authoredTrackColumnSizes = authoredGridTrackSizes(node, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns, columnWidths.size());
1755 FloatLine previousColumnEndLine;
1756 for (unsigned i = 0; i < columnPositions.size(); ++i) {
1757 auto columnStartLine = columnLineAt(columnPositions[i]);
1758
1759 if (gridOverlay.config.showExtendedGridLines) {
1760 auto extendedLine = columnStartLine.extendedToBounds(viewportBounds);
1761 gridHighlightOverlay.gridLines.append(extendedLine);
1762 } else {
1763 gridHighlightOverlay.gridLines.append(columnStartLine);
1764 }
1765
1766 FloatLine gapLabelLine = columnStartLine;
1767 if (i) {
1768 gridHighlightOverlay.gaps.append({ previousColumnEndLine.start(), columnStartLine.start(), columnStartLine.end(), previousColumnEndLine.end() });
1769 FloatLine lineBetweenColumnTops = { columnStartLine.start(), previousColumnEndLine.start() };
1770 FloatLine lineBetweenColumnBottoms = { columnStartLine.end(), previousColumnEndLine.end() };
1771 gapLabelLine = { lineBetweenColumnTops.pointAtRelativeDistance(0.5), lineBetweenColumnBottoms.pointAtRelativeDistance(0.5) };
1772 }
1773
1774 if (i < columnWidths.size() && i < columnPositions.size()) {
1775 auto width = columnWidths[i];
1776 auto columnEndLine = columnLineAt(columnPositions[i] + width);
1777
1778 if (gridOverlay.config.showExtendedGridLines) {
1779 auto extendedLine = columnEndLine.extendedToBounds(viewportBounds);
1780 gridHighlightOverlay.gridLines.append(extendedLine);
1781 } else {
1782 gridHighlightOverlay.gridLines.append(columnEndLine);
1783 }
1784 previousColumnEndLine = columnEndLine;
1785
1786 if (gridOverlay.config.showTrackSizes) {
1787 auto authoredTrackSize = i < authoredTrackColumnSizes.size() ? authoredTrackColumnSizes[i] : "auto"_s;
1788 FloatLine trackTopLine = { columnStartLine.start(), columnEndLine.start() };
1789 gridHighlightOverlay.labels.append(buildLabel(authoredTrackSize, trackTopLine.pointAtRelativeDistance(0.5), translucentLabelBackgroundColor, correctedArrowDirection(LabelArrowDirection::Up, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns), LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle));
1790 }
1791 } else
1792 previousColumnEndLine = columnStartLine;
1793
1794 StringBuilder lineLabel;
1795 if (gridOverlay.config.showLineNumbers) {
1796 lineLabel.append(i + 1);
1797 if (i <= authoredTrackColumnSizes.size())
1798 lineLabel.append(emSpace, -static_cast<int>(authoredTrackColumnSizes.size() - i + 1));
1799 }
1800 if (gridOverlay.config.showLineNames && columnLineNames.contains(i)) {
1801 for (auto lineName : columnLineNames.get(i)) {
1802 if (!lineLabel.isEmpty())
1803 lineLabel.append(thinSpace, bullet, thinSpace);
1804 lineLabel.append(lineName);
1805 }
1806 }
1807
1808 if (!lineLabel.isEmpty()) {
1809 auto text = lineLabel.toString();
1810 auto arrowDirection = correctedArrowDirection(LabelArrowDirection::Down, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns);
1811 auto arrowEdgePosition = correctedArrowEdgePosition(LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns);
1812
1813 if (!i)
1814 arrowEdgePosition = correctedArrowEdgePosition(LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns);
1815 else if (i == columnPositions.size() - 1)
1816 arrowEdgePosition = correctedArrowEdgePosition(LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns);
1817
1818 auto expectedLabelSize = expectedSizeForLayoutLabel(text, arrowDirection);
1819 auto gapLabelPosition = gapLabelLine.start();
1820
1821 // The area under the window's toolbar is drawable, but not meaningfully visible, so we must account for that space.
1822 auto topEdgeInset = pageView->topContentInset(ScrollView::TopContentInsetType::WebCoreOrPlatformContentInset);
1823 if (gapLabelLine.start().y() - expectedLabelSize.height() - topEdgeInset + scrollPosition.y() - viewportBounds.y() < 0) {
1824 arrowDirection = correctedArrowDirection(LabelArrowDirection::Up, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForColumns);
1825
1826 // Special case for the first column to make sure the label will be out of the way of the first row's label.
1827 // The label heights will be the same, as they use the same font, so moving down by this label's size will
1828 // create enough space for this special circumstance.
1829 if (!i)
1830 gapLabelPosition = gapLabelLine.pointAtAbsoluteDistance(expectedLabelSize.height());
1831 }
1832
1833 gridHighlightOverlay.labels.append(buildLabel(text, gapLabelPosition, translucentLabelBackgroundColor, arrowDirection, arrowEdgePosition));
1834 }
1835 }
1836
1837 auto rowHeights = renderGrid.trackSizesForComputedStyle(GridTrackSizingDirection::ForRows);
1838 auto rowLineNames = gridLineNames(node->renderStyle(), GridTrackSizingDirection::ForRows, rowPositions.size());
1839 auto authoredTrackRowSizes = authoredGridTrackSizes(node, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForRows, rowHeights.size());
1840 FloatLine previousRowEndLine;
1841 for (unsigned i = 0; i < rowPositions.size(); ++i) {
1842 auto rowStartLine = rowLineAt(rowPositions[i]);
1843
1844 if (gridOverlay.config.showExtendedGridLines) {
1845 auto extendedLine = rowStartLine.extendedToBounds(viewportBounds);
1846 gridHighlightOverlay.gridLines.append(extendedLine);
1847 } else {
1848 gridHighlightOverlay.gridLines.append(rowStartLine);
1849 }
1850
1851 FloatPoint gapLabelPosition = rowStartLine.start();
1852 if (i) {
1853 FloatLine lineBetweenRowStarts = { rowStartLine.start(), previousRowEndLine.start() };
1854 gridHighlightOverlay.gaps.append({ previousRowEndLine.start(), previousRowEndLine.end(), rowStartLine.end(), rowStartLine.start() });
1855 gapLabelPosition = lineBetweenRowStarts.pointAtRelativeDistance(0.5);
1856 }
1857
1858 if (i < rowHeights.size() && i < rowPositions.size()) {
1859 auto height = rowHeights[i];
1860 auto rowEndLine = rowLineAt(rowPositions[i] + height);
1861
1862 if (gridOverlay.config.showExtendedGridLines) {
1863 auto extendedLine = rowEndLine.extendedToBounds(viewportBounds);
1864 gridHighlightOverlay.gridLines.append(extendedLine);
1865 } else {
1866 gridHighlightOverlay.gridLines.append(rowEndLine);
1867 }
1868 previousRowEndLine = rowEndLine;
1869
1870 if (gridOverlay.config.showTrackSizes) {
1871 auto authoredTrackSize = i < authoredTrackRowSizes.size() ? authoredTrackRowSizes[i] : "auto"_s;
1872 FloatLine trackLeftLine = { rowStartLine.start(), rowEndLine.start() };
1873 gridHighlightOverlay.labels.append(buildLabel(authoredTrackSize, trackLeftLine.pointAtRelativeDistance(0.5), translucentLabelBackgroundColor, correctedArrowDirection(LabelArrowDirection::Left, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForRows), LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle));
1874 }
1875 } else
1876 previousRowEndLine = rowStartLine;
1877
1878 StringBuilder lineLabel;
1879 if (gridOverlay.config.showLineNumbers) {
1880 lineLabel.append(i + 1);
1881 if (i <= authoredTrackRowSizes.size())
1882 lineLabel.append(emSpace, -static_cast<int>(authoredTrackRowSizes.size() - i + 1));
1883 }
1884 if (gridOverlay.config.showLineNames && rowLineNames.contains(i)) {
1885 for (auto lineName : rowLineNames.get(i)) {
1886 if (!lineLabel.isEmpty())
1887 lineLabel.append(thinSpace, bullet, thinSpace);
1888 lineLabel.append(lineName);
1889 }
1890 }
1891
1892 if (!lineLabel.isEmpty()) {
1893 auto text = lineLabel.toString();
1894 auto arrowDirection = correctedArrowDirection(LabelArrowDirection::Right, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForRows);
1895 auto arrowEdgePosition = correctedArrowEdgePosition(LabelArrowEdgePosition::Middle, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForRows);
1896
1897 if (!i)
1898 arrowEdgePosition = correctedArrowEdgePosition(LabelArrowEdgePosition::Leading, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForRows);
1899 else if (i == rowPositions.size() - 1)
1900 arrowEdgePosition = correctedArrowEdgePosition(LabelArrowEdgePosition::Trailing, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForRows);
1901
1902 auto expectedLabelSize = expectedSizeForLayoutLabel(text, arrowDirection);
1903 if (gapLabelPosition.x() - expectedLabelSize.width() + scrollPosition.x() - viewportBounds.x() < 0)
1904 arrowDirection = correctedArrowDirection(LabelArrowDirection::Left, GridTrackSizingDirection::ForRows);
1905
1906 gridHighlightOverlay.labels.append(buildLabel(text, gapLabelPosition, translucentLabelBackgroundColor, arrowDirection, arrowEdgePosition));
1907 }
1908 }
1909
1910 if (gridOverlay.config.showAreaNames) {
1911 for (auto& gridArea : node->renderStyle()->namedGridArea()) {
1912 auto& name = gridArea.key;
1913 auto& area = gridArea.value;
1914
1915 // Named grid areas will always be rectangular per the CSS Grid specification.
1916 auto columnStartLine = columnLineAt(columnPositions[area.columns.startLine()]);
1917 auto columnEndLine = columnLineAt(columnPositions[area.columns.endLine() - 1] + columnWidths[area.columns.endLine() - 1]);
1918 auto rowStartLine = rowLineAt(rowPositions[area.rows.startLine()]);
1919 auto rowEndLine = rowLineAt(rowPositions[area.rows.endLine() - 1] + rowHeights[area.rows.endLine() - 1]);
1920
1921 std::optional<FloatPoint> topLeft = columnStartLine.intersectionWith(rowStartLine);
1922 std::optional<FloatPoint> topRight = columnEndLine.intersectionWith(rowStartLine);
1923 std::optional<FloatPoint> bottomRight = columnEndLine.intersectionWith(rowEndLine);
1924 std::optional<FloatPoint> bottomLeft = columnStartLine.intersectionWith(rowEndLine);
1925
1926 // If any two lines are coincident with each other, they will not have an intersection, which can occur with extreme `transform: perspective(...)` values.
1927 if (!topLeft || !topRight || !bottomRight || !bottomLeft)
1928 continue;
1929
1930 InspectorOverlay::Highlight::GridHighlightOverlay::Area highlightOverlayArea;
1931 highlightOverlayArea.name = name;
1932 highlightOverlayArea.quad = { *topLeft, *topRight, *bottomRight, *bottomLeft };
1933 gridHighlightOverlay.areas.append(highlightOverlayArea);
1934 }
1935 }
1936
1937 return { gridHighlightOverlay };
1938}
